Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with oar symbol.
Type series: KT1264 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 184, 5. Names, [Amyntas], Charmokrates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0314)
